# Plan 119 — committed override allowlist for the dependency-safety gate
# (tools/dependency_safety.py). Mirrors the .trivyignore precedent: an
# override is a committed, code-reviewed entry with a dated justification,
# never an ephemeral PR label (a label applied after PR creation would not
# re-run the dependency-safety job — see docs/plans/119-dependency-bump-
# safety-gate.md §2).
#
# One finding key per line. A finding's key is printed in its BLOCK message
# (format: "<watched-file>:<identifier>", e.g.
# "docker-compose.yml:postgis/postgis" or "pyproject.toml:requires-python").
# Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
#
# --- No active entries as of 2026-07-15 ---
# Add an entry here only after the flagged bump has been verified safe
# (e.g. the target migration from Plan 118 has been executed on the target
# host), with a dated comment explaining why and pointing at the plan/PR
# that did the verification.
